                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kreeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-01-21T10:00:00-03:50"
                            >January 21, 1930—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. The Minister for Foreign Affairs informs me that the Cabinet believes it
                    necessary to notify League of Nations of the late Bolivian movement toward war,
                    as neutrals unfortunately are to date without organization. He will advise
                    therefore the Secretariat this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kreeck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
